condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :5.01(a) | Description :RD has established the FPU with organization, qualifications and TOR satisfactory to theBank | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :5.01(b) | Description :The Borrower has submitted to the Bank the Operations Manual in form and substancesatisfactory to the Bank | Due Date :01-Oct-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 I.A.2 | Description :TRRC shall carry out the financial management and disbursement for the Projectin accordance with the Project Implementation Agreement | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 I.A.2 | Description :The Borrower shall maintain the TRRC with terms of reference, resources andstaff necessary for proper Project implementation and satisfactory to the Bank | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 I.A.4 | Description :The Borrower shall permit the use of standards for construction, planning anddesign of highways adopted by the European Union (in addition to the national standards), acceptable to the Bank, in the design,construction and maintenance of the road works under theProject. | Due Date :30-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 I.A.6 | Description :The Borrower shall, through the RD, recruit a financial auditor under terms ofreference and conditions satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date :31-Dec-2009
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 I.C.1 | Description :The Borrower shall ensure the Project is carried out in accordance with theprovisions of the EIA, EMP, RPF and RAP | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 II.A | Description :The Borrower shall, through RD, monitor and evaluate the progress of the Projectand prepare Project Reports in accordance with theprovisions of Section 5.08 of the General Conditions | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 II.B.1 | Description :The Borrower shall, through RD, maintain or cause to be maintained a financialmanagement system in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.09 of the General Conditions | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 II.B.2 | Description :The Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank not later than forty five(45) days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 II.B.3 | Description :The Borrower shall cause RD to have its Financial Statements related to theProject audited in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.09 (b) of the General Conditions. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.A.5 | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that adequate budgetary resources are made availablefor the Project in the Borrower's annual budget for the duration of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2.I.C.2 | Description :The Borrower shall, prior to the commencement of works under the Project, ensurethat: (a) the provisions of the EMP are adequatelyincluded in the proposed contract(s) for said works; and (b) the owners and usersof the land where said works are to be implementedare fully compensated in accordance with the provisions of the RAP. | Due Date:30-Sep-2009
